comments.body:
@rhatdan I understand, as an alternative would it be possible to add an environment variable to force podman to only recognize config files in the specified directory? Similar to the behavior of the --config-dir flag I mentioned previously. This would disable the merging/referencing behavior where instead of searching /usr, then /etc, then $XDG_CONFIG_HOME paths for configs
podman would simply only recognize configs in the specific directory.

Having the guarantee that only configuration files in a certain directory are parsed (regardless of the way that the directory is specified) would be immensely useful.
